                      "name": "Cleansing Bell",
                      "type": "custom_entry"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type": "paragraph"
                },
                {
                  "alignment": "center",
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "styles": [
                        "bold",
                        "color:rgb(255, 255, 255)"
                      ],
                      "text": "Archon War",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "level": 1,
                  "type": "heading"
                },
                {
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "alignment": "left",
                      "type": "custom_image",
                      "url": "https://act-upload.hoyoverse.com/event-ugc-hoyowiki/2024/01/11/178140791/88a38e9fdf707c65b3edfabfe47a18f3_1593369701320699257.PNG"
                    },
                    {
                      "text": "Guizhong was quite the visionary but tragically passed before her time. It later came to pass that an all-consuming war erupted between the gods, whose reach none in Teyvat could escape. Soon, the Guili Plains had become engulfed in war. Thereupon the Guili Plains did the gods do battle, black dust choked the heavens and a thousand rocks splintered. Though the Adepti fought to protect the",
                      "type": "text"
                    },
                    {
                      "text": "Guili Plains, they could not stop the tide of war, which ravaged the plains. Guizhong was overpowered by the enemy and fell in battle. Guizhong asked the Geo Archon to forget about the challenge she left for him in the stone dumbbell.",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type": "paragraph"
                },
                {
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "text": "Before her return to the elements, the Yakshas and Adepti worked together to contain the residual energy expelled by the departed deity. The Geo Archon still made attempts to unlock the stone dumbbell but was unable to do so even after many years. It is said that her final smile was a lonely one, even as her form dissolved into the finest dust. After Guizhong's death, the Geo Archon took his people south of Mt. Tianheng. Thus the people departed from the Guili Plains for good, never to return, and it was left to become a wilderness. As for the Cleansing Bell, the Geo Archon granted it to Streetward Rambler for safekeeping to honor Guizhong's memory. Each time Streetward Rambler rang the Cleansing Bell, it was to play the tune that Guizhong composed on it. Guizhong's manuscripts still lie unfinished in the Realm of Clouds. The blank pages give Cloud Retainer cause for contemplation on what might have been. Over the years, the wild Glaze Lilies dwindled till at last they were no more.",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type": "paragraph"
                },
                {
                  "content": [
